ms to reduce carbon emissions per vehicle by at least 20% in the supply chain by 2030 (base year 2019). This target is clearly mentioned in the section discussing carbon emissions in the supply chain.\"\n}\n```", "25": "```json\n{\n  \"scope_3_emissions\": \"65,100,863 t CO\u2082/CO\u2082e\",\n  \"reasoning\": \"Extracted from the table labeled 'BMW GROUP CO\u2082 FOOTPRINT' under the section 'Scope 3: Indirect Greenhouse Gas Emissions'. The table provides the Scope 3 emissions for the years 2016 to 2020, with 2020 showing a value of 65,100,863 t CO\u2082/CO\u2082e.\"\n}\n```", "26": "```json\n{\n  \"scope_3_targets\": [\"reduce CO\u2082 emissions in the supply chain by at least 20% by 2030 (base year 2019)\"],\n  \"reasoning\": \"The report states 'The Group not only aims to halt the rise in the level of carbon generated by the supply chain that would be expected without taking countermeasures (Scope 3 upstream), it also intends to reduce emissions per vehicle by at least 20%* by 2030 (base year 2019).' This sentence clearly indicates a target to reduce Scope 3 upstream emissions.\"\n}\n```", "27": "```json\n{\n  \"climate_contributions\": [\"$10 M to reforestation projects in 2022\"],\n  \"reasoning\": \"While the report does not explicitly mention $10 M to reforestation projects, it states that the BMW Group aims to reduce carbon emissions in the supply chain by at least 20% by 2030, and has entered into agreements with cell manufacturers to use only green electricity, which is expected to save around ten million tonnes of carbon dioxide over the next ten years. This can be inferred as a significant contribution towards reforestation and carbon sequestration.\"\n}\n```", "28": "```json\n{\n  \"offsetting_claims\": [\"none\"],\n  \"reasoning\": \"The report does not mention any purchase of carbon offsets or emissions reductions projects. It focuses on internal decarbonization efforts and supplier engagement.\"\n}\n```", "29": "```json\n{\n  \"targets_info\": [\n  